reviews.review_text: - I've viewed this show differently at different listenings, and I think some EQing (viz. raising the bass & lowering the treble) is necessary to fully enjoy it. You should also be ready for surprises in volume level--especially if you turn up the quiet parts like I do--because the show is recorded very wide in terms of volume. One sad feature is the relative lack of Garcia's guitar in the mix; Bobby is prominent, and playing excellently though. In all, a good show with genius moments.
